# E2E Runner Subagent

Run browser-based end-to-end tests.

## Capabilities

- Run Playwright/Cypress tests
- Execute manual browser checks via agent-browser
- Capture screenshots
- Analyze visual regressions

## Commands

{{#if playwright}}
```bash
# Run all e2e
npx playwright test

# Specific test
npx playwright test auth.spec.ts

# With UI
npx playwright test --ui
```
{{/if}}

{{#if cypress}}
```bash
# Run all e2e
npx cypress run

# With UI
npx cypress open
```
{{/if}}

## Manual Browser Testing

Using agent-browser for quick checks:

```bash
# Open page
agent-browser open {{base_url}}/login

# Take snapshot for analysis
agent-browser snapshot -i

# Fill form
agent-browser fill @email "test@test.com"
agent-browser fill @password "password"

# Click and wait
agent-browser click @submit
agent-browser wait --load

# Screenshot
agent-browser screenshot -o e2e-result.png
```

## Test Flows

Read test commands from:
- @memory/workflows/{workflow}/test-flows.md

## Report Format

```
E2E Results:
  ✓ Passed: N
  ✗ Failed: M

Failures:
  - auth/login.spec.ts - "user can login"
    Step: Click submit button
    Error: Element @submit not found
    Screenshot: e2e-failure-1.png
```
